{"task_summary":"Write a Python function that deduplicates customer records by email, keeping the most recent timestamp.","approach":"I started by creating a dictionary to store the emails as keys and the timestamps as values. I then iterated through each record in the input data. If an email is already present in my dictionary, I compared its timestamp with the new one. If it was more recent than the old one, I updated the value of that key. Otherwise, I added a new entry to the dictionary.","code":"import json

def deduplicate(data):
    # Create a dictionary to store email:timestamp pairs.
    emails = {}

    for record in data:
        # If an email is already present in our dictionary,
        if record["email"] in emails.keys():
            # Compare the timestamps of each record with that of the one stored in the dict.
            if record["timestamp"] > emails[record["email"]]:
                # Update the timestamp value for this email.
                emails[record["email"]] = record["timestamp"]
        else:
            # Otherwise, add a new entry to our dictionary with this email and its timestamp.
            emails[record["email"]] = record["timestamp"]
    return json.dumps(emails)

if __name__ == "__main__":
    print(deduplicate([{
        "email":"<EMAIL>",
        "timestamp":"2018-05-31T14:19:19+00:00"
    },
    {
        "email":"<EMAIL>",
        "timestamp":"2017-06-01T14:19:19+00:00"
    }]))
","complexity":{"time":"O(n)","space":"O(n)"},"edge_cases":["No edge cases."],"tests":["import json

def deduplicate(data):
    # Create a dictionary to store email:timestamp pairs.
    emails = {}

    for record in data:
        # If an email is already present in our dictionary,
        if record["email"] in emails.keys():
            # Compare the timestamps of each record with that of the one stored in the dict.
            if record["timestamp"] > emails[record["email"]]:
                # Update the timestamp value for this email.
                emails[record["email"]] = record["timestamp"]
        else:
            # Otherwise, add a new entry to our dictionary with this email and its timestamp.
            emails[record["email"]] = record["timestamp"]
    return json.dumps(emails)

