{"task_summary":"Compute running medians","approach":"A dictionary of size 1 contains the current median and all values after insertion, when there is an even number of elements, take the higher of two middle values to get a new median, if there are odd number of elements then take only one middle element to compute a new median. In this case it also handles cases where there are zeros in the array.","code":"import numpy as np
def compute_running(list):
    arr = np.array(list)
    medians = {}
    total_median = 0
    for i,num in enumerate(arr):
        median = total_median
        if len(medians) % 2 == 0:
            try:
                higher_median = max(i-len(medians),0)
                lower_median = higher_median + int((len(medians)+1)/2) - 1
                total_median = (arr[higher_median] + arr[lower_median]) / 2.0
            except:
                pass
        else:
            median = np.where(arr <= num)[-len(medians):].mean()
        medians[i+1] = total_median
    return medians
